{
  "stem": "22840.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I passed as a-- as a child of one of their family who was killed during the war, not in an army, just-- just killed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He and his wife, and they took me to their house, and I'm part of their family now.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they treated me as such.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I knew that all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew that before I came there, that I should not go with children-- with other children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that-- that not even-- that I knew before I came, to beware of other Christian children that accidentally will discover I'm Jewish, and they just beat me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think that he-- my father was very well known in the community and highly respected.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He met my mother in Banksa Bystrica and she was, from all the description, nice looking, very intelligent, very warm person.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were two children, took pity on, they just took pity on us, in a sense, that we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Jews helped each other as much as they can.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think he was in his 20s.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He-- he's in his 70s now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] also did more than that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every Jew that he met-- after he place me, every Jew that he met, he told him that the son of [INAUDIBLE] Frieder, or Rabbi Frieder, is in this village, in this house, and spread the word.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Indeed, my father, who was in jail, got the word in jail that I am alive and that his wife and daughter were killed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the-- the word did spread, and without-- without Henry, he would not discover me.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
